    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="315"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9315 Manchuria/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-13">October 13,
                            1935</date>.<lb/>[Received October 13—12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>454. According to an official Tass report in the <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi>
                    October 13th Japanese Manchurian divisions crossed the Soviet frontier on 6th,
                    8th, and 12th of October and fired on Soviet border guards. Skirmish on October
                    12th included rifle and machine-gun fire and casualties reported. The Soviet
                    Government has protested to Tokyo and has proposed naming a mixed commission for
                    investigation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shantz</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
